data.title: Summer Picnics 2024
data.meta_description: Summer picnics are fun, casual get togethers for Grinnellians. They are hosted by fellow Grinnell alumni and friends along with the Office of Development and Alumni Relations.
data.text:
Grinnell-in-Des Moines Summer Picnic

Louise Alcorn ’92, Kathleen Ely ’93, Cindy Kadenge ’90, Renee Bourgeois Parsons ’96, Jason Parsons ’96, and the Office of Development and Alumni Relations invite you to the Grinnell-in-Des Moines summer picnic.

Summer picnics are fun, casual get togethers for Grinnellians. All members of the Grinnell Community — alumni, current students, incoming new students, family members, and friends — are welcome at summer picnics.

Grinnell Summer Picnic

5–7 p.m. | Saturday, June 22

Lions Park

Ralph Whitten Shelter

72nd Street and Aurora Avenue

Urbandale, IA 50322

Register online or by phone at 866-850-1846 by Wednesday, June 19 at 11:59 p.m. CT.

Potluck and parking information will be included in your confirmation email.
